Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.31,0:01:45.66,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.16,0:01:48.87,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Taking your sweet time to \Nanalyze the situation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.18,0:01:51.33,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You want to get this over with, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.33,0:01:52.84,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.53,0:01:55.05,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just as I suspected... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.65,0:01:59.67,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He didn’t simply make Kurosaki’s \NFullbring his own... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.67,0:02:01.43,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His attacks are combined with the{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.43,0:02:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}power of Kurosaki’s \NSpiritual Pressure...!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.73,0:02:06.29,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is going to be a problem... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.29,0:02:08.52,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So, did you come up \Nwith any great ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.42,0:02:11.27,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.51,0:02:12.92,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.92,0:02:15.69,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re the one who suggested \Nwe analyze the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.69,0:02:18.78,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Weren’t you trying to come with \Nan idea to quickly take him down?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.35,0:02:21.38,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.38,0:02:23.37,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,There’s no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.86,0:02:25.83,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What? There isn’t?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.83,0:02:29.43,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,I was observing his Spiritual Pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.87,0:02:31.45,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.45,0:02:33.16,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,His Spiritual Pressure contains your...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.16,0:02:35.19,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I’ll be going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.75,0:02:37.26,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.67,0:02:40.76,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that his attack is combined \Nwith your Spiritual Pressure means...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.96,0:02:45.60,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you finally decided to come out...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.60,0:02:46.84,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.84,0:02:50.60,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you come with a plan \Nwhile you were hiding?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.60,0:02:52.16,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I just checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.16,0:02:54.98,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,He didn’t have any, so I came on out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:02:59.57,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,A Getsugatensho, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.57,0:03:01.00,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:03.66,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I almost died because \Nof that the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.24,0:03:08.12,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,If you’re going to beat me, I \Nsuppose that’s the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.38,0:03:10.14,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t do it, Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.14,0:03:11.12,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,He’s egging you on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Getsugatensho!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:42.33,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that he has your Spiritual \NPressure combined with his own
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.33,0:03:45.49,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,means it’s possible that he can \Nalso use your techniques...!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.21,0:03:47.92,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening, Kurosaki?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.62,0:03:49.62,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.62,0:03:50.81,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Quit nagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.81,0:03:52.46,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Who’s nagging?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.96,0:03:56.64,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You have a bad habit of not \Nhearing people through!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:58.90,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Listening to you won’t change a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:01.51,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not as though that’s \Ngoing to diminish his powers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:02.64,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,It does change things...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.64,0:04:04.13,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,At least you can be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.29,0:04:07.71,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Watch it, Kurosaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.71,0:04:10.06,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,His last blow made it very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.06,0:04:14.40,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn’t just your Spiritual \NPressure and Fullbring that he took.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.18,0:04:19.44,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,He’s probably acquired every \None of your abilities...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.46,0:04:26.95,Default,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,How cruel of you…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.01,0:04:33.91,Default,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Am I not…your benefactor…?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.20,0:04:41.07,Default,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn’t it pain your \Nheart to do this…?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.63,0:04:44.28,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,You are indeed my benefactor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:46.38,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,And I do appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.31,0:04:49.91,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,However, you are Ichigo \NKurosaki’s enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:54.02,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,I will not hesitate to kill that enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.45,0:04:56.86,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.88,0:05:05.81,Default,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Damn…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:21.80,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Good, you’re finally out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.06,0:05:24.67,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Captain! You got out pretty quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.67,0:05:27.57,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up. You’re just slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.23,0:05:32.42,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Abarai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.42,0:05:34.99,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to you? You’re a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:36.44,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,You look pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.92,0:05:38.41,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:42.27,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,I escaped that dimension quite \Na while ago via the explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.27,0:05:44.02,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,but I was unable to move \Nfor some time, so…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.02,0:05:47.51,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that huge explosion \Ncame from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.51,0:05:49.16,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,What about your opponent? \NDid you kill them?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.88,0:05:53.83,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,She’s dead… I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.83,0:05:56.07,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.07,0:05:57.86,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, well…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.86,0:06:01.29,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,He disappeared after I \Nscolded him a little…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.29,0:06:03.01,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Scolded him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.47,0:06:06.33,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why you took so long!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.33,0:06:07.88,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Taking your damn sweet time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.88,0:06:09.26,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sir…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.57,0:06:13.26,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why’re you guys arguing \Nthe minute you show up…?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:14.47,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.47,0:06:16.87,Default,KENPACHI,0000,0000,0000,,This is none of your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.87,0:06:19.16,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You’re right. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.72,0:06:21.46,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Get it out of your system.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.27,0:06:25.57,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! This wasn’t part of the deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.57,0:06:29.06,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,You said you’d free me \Nonce I shut down my powers!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:32.14,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Once we confirm that \Neveryone is free, we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.97,0:06:34.87,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Kuchiki and Kuchiki aren’t here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.46,0:06:37.33,Default,IKKAKU,0000,0000,0000,,Can you refer to them \Nby first names, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.33,0:06:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re confusing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.67,0:06:41.99,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m losing feeling \Nin my arms and legs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.35,0:06:44.00,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.23,0:06:46.27,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,Look after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.27,0:06:47.28,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.28,0:06:48.38,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Is she all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.38,0:06:49.84,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,She’s alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.31,0:06:51.77,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,Her wounds are slight,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.77,0:06:53.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there isn’t any irregularity \Nin her Spiritual Pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.84,0:06:54.85,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,However…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.85,0:06:57.23,Default,BYAKUYA,0000,0000,0000,,there were no signs of \Nthe enemy or its corpse
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.23,0:06:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the area where Rukia collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.25,0:07:04.85,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you know something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.85,0:07:06.23,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.46,0:07:09.61,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,I hardly know anything about \NRiruka’s abilities…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.61,0:07:11.99,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Neither of us wanted to show \Nthe other our abilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.98,0:07:15.28,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t know if she’s \Ndead, or if she got away,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.28,0:07:17.55,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,but I’d be grateful if she were dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.24,0:07:21.07,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Come on! Isn’t this enough?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.07,0:07:22.50,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Melt this ice already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:23.85,Default,HITSUGAYA,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.85,0:07:25.17,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.84,0:07:32.36,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can’t undo that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.46,0:07:36.43,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.43,0:07:37.44,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.44,0:07:41.39,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Fullbringers and Substitute Soul \NReapers can trade their powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:45.58,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,When we first joined Kugo, \Nwe traded a portion
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.58,0:07:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of our powers with each \Nother as a sign of loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:50.74,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,We also placed a small \Nrestriction on those powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.41,0:07:53.54,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Here’s the restriction \NI share between Kugo…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:56.66,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,“If Kugo is within the \Nrange of my abilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.12,0:08:01.04,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,then I cannot undo them \Nunless he orders me to.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:11.02,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.02,0:08:12.85,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You put yourself at \Nquite a risk, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.85,0:08:14.77,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I had no such intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.21,0:08:16.65,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.65,0:08:19.22,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You’re just fighting with \Neverything you’ve got, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.87,0:08:23.17,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,So, what are you fighting for right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.98,0:08:24.69,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:27.65,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukishima’s dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:37.32,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, he’s not dead yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.32,0:08:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but his Spiritual \NPressure is nearly gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.14,0:08:42.44,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I’d say he only has about \Nten minutes to live…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.13,0:08:44.00,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,And…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:48.69,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,when a Fullbringer dies, all traces \Nof his abilities disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.30,0:08:51.06,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Understand what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.06,0:08:53.06,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,If Tsukishima dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.06,0:08:54.99,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,all of the memories of the past that he
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.99,0:08:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,inserted will return to \Nwhat they used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:08:59.61,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Your family and friends will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.61,0:09:02.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all be just the way they were before.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.13,0:09:04.75,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,So I’ll ask you once more:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.47,0:09:08.61,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, what are you fighting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:14.24,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,No answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.80,0:09:16.85,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Then let me tell you one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:21.89,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s about the enemy you \Nshould really be fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.07,0:09:32.95,Default,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,They’ve stabilized…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.95,0:09:34.04,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.63,0:09:35.80,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Tessai,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.80,0:09:37.42,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.42,0:09:39.49,Default,TESSAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I will see to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.49,0:09:40.88,Default,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.34,0:09:42.72,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,To where everyone is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:45.23,Default,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,To assist? I’m coming with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.62,0:09:48.01,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,No, most of the fighting \Nis probably over,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.01,0:09:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I’m going to provide healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.26,0:09:54.23,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll be of no help, \NIsshin, so stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.19,0:09:57.63,Default,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn’t we try to \Nwrap this up quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.63,0:10:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by assisting Ichigo with his fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.38,0:10:01.44,Default,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,If we don’t do that, then…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.44,0:10:04.37,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,He’ll find out from Kugo Ginjo?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.82,0:10:07.96,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,That’s fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.53,0:10:12.75,Default,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,He was going to find \Nout sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.93,0:10:18.18,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy I should really be fighting?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.91,0:10:20.18,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.18,0:10:21.67,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t mess with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.67,0:10:24.89,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve had enough of your mind games!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.89,0:10:26.26,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.22,0:10:29.02,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,You see yourself in at a disadvantage,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.02,0:10:31.60,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,so you present a shocking “fact”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.60,0:10:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to lay on the psychological pressure
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.61,0:10:36.81,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,in order to make your point that
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.81,0:10:39.30,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,“You’d be better off \Njoining with me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.88,0:10:40.98,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.38,0:10:42.78,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,At a disadvantage, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.71,0:10:46.03,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What ever makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.03,0:10:50.25,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I can fully defeat \Nthe both of you right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.05,0:10:53.20,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why don’t you try shooting \Nat me from the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.20,0:10:55.46,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll parry your shots while \Nkeeping our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.97,0:10:59.94,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.51,0:11:04.97,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know why you were \Nentrusted with a Combat Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.49,0:11:08.89,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.20,0:11:11.83,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,When you were handed the Combat Pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.83,0:11:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you must’ve been told \Nsomething like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:18.18,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,“If the Soul Reaper is deemed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.18,0:11:21.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,beneficial to the Soul Society,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.12,0:11:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is customary to give \Nthem the Combat Pass.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.15,0:11:27.24,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Listen closely, Kurosaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.10,0:11:29.66,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.76,0:11:33.63,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It’s no simple task for an {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.63,0:11:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}organization to determine whether {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.48,0:11:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}someone will be of benefit \Nor a detriment…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.58,0:11:41.11,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And the biggest issue is that if they {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.11,0:11:44.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}“hand out Combat Passes \Nto those of benefit,”{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.90,0:11:47.45,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they’ve never told \NKurosaki what happens {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.45,0:11:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to those who are not.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.75,0:11:52.20,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,More correctly…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.20,0:11:53.87,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Whether someone is of benefit or
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.87,0:11:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,detriment to the Soul Society \Nhas nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:12:00.57,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Combat Passes are handed \Nout equally regardless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.74,0:12:03.99,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The official name for Combat Pass is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.99,0:12:06.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“Substitute Soul Reaper \NCombat Pass”…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.89,0:12:09.54,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It certifies that one has permission to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.54,0:12:12.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,conduct Substitute Soul Reaper \Nduties in the World of the Living.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.01,0:12:14.12,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.53,0:12:19.05,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,But have you ever, to this moment, \Ntruly felt its authority?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.67,0:12:23.65,Default,ICHIGO (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am Ichigo Kurosaki! I’m \Na Substitute Soul Reaper! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.65,0:12:25.51,Default,ICHIGO (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here’s my Combat Pass! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.51,0:12:27.09,Default,KURUMADANI (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What the hell is that? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.09,0:12:30.43,Default,KURUMADANI (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I’ve never seen or \Nheard of such a thing. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.42,0:12:32.64,Default,ICHIGO'S VOICE (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What’s with this thing? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.05,0:12:35.49,Default,ICHIGO'S VOICE (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It isn’t any help at all… {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.55,0:12:41.85,Default,ISHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying the Combat \NPass has another function?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.85,0:12:42.73,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:45.19,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The function of the Combat Pass is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.19,0:12:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep watch and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:49.26,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to the Combat Pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.26,0:12:50.85,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,the Soul Society is able to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.85,0:12:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,keep constant tabs on your whereabouts,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.88,0:12:57.04,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,and allowed them to control \Nyour Spiritual Pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.04,0:12:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at least while you had \Nthe Combat Pass near you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.67,0:13:02.30,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn’t you ever question…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.78,0:13:04.47,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why your Spiritual Pressure that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rages out of control \Nwhen you’re agitated,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.34,0:13:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even in Soul Reaper form, \Nnever had any effect
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.89,0:13:12.56,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,on you when you were in human form?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.86,0:13:17.06,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why, when you used your Combat \NPass to produce your Fullbring,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.06,0:13:21.15,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,your Spiritual Pressure gushed \Nforth from the Combat Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.17,0:13:24.31,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why, during your Fullbring training,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.31,0:13:28.45,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,you heard your friends voices \Nvia the Combat Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:32.37,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you must’ve \Nquestioned them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.50,0:13:36.93,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The Combat Pass is a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.93,0:13:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,device that communicates \Nwith the Soul Society,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:41.82,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,absorbing your Spiritual Pressure,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.82,0:13:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then analyzing and controlling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.90,0:13:47.54,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You were given that so the Soul Society
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.54,0:13:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could keep watch on you and control you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.93,0:13:54.50,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not that you never \Nfelt it was strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.61,0:13:59.77,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You simply pushed those questions \Ninto the back of your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.92,0:14:03.84,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,People who you bonded with in battle
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.84,0:14:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would never do that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.00,0:14:10.78,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You didn’t want to believe \Nthey would do that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.51,0:14:12.65,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.61,0:14:15.88,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I will tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.52,0:14:18.86,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The man who came up \Nwith this plan is…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.83,0:14:21.91,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Jushiro Ukitake…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.91,0:14:24.13,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The Captain of Squad 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.69,0:14:32.34,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,The Combat Pass?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.81,0:14:36.18,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.63,0:14:38.75,Default,UKITAKE (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Soul Society also has a law {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.75,0:14:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}covering the emergence of \Na Substitute Soul Reaper.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.73,0:14:44.47,Default,UKITAKE (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It has been decided since \Nancient times that if{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the Substitute Soul Reaper is {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.91,0:14:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}deemed beneficial to the Soul Society…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.63,0:14:51.54,Default,UKITAKE (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}then we are to give this to them. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.39,0:14:54.22,Default,UKITAKE (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That one is yours now. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.22,0:14:55.84,Default,ICHIGO (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see… {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.84,0:14:57.58,Default,ICHIGO (flashback),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you, Ukitake. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.90,0:15:10.38,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ukitake did…?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.08,0:15:14.85,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,We were tricked by the \Nmost peace-loving man
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.85,0:15:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,among the 13 Court Guard Squads!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.30,0:15:18.62,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:24.61,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,The man’s aim is to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.61,0:15:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,watch and control us in order to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.45,0:15:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,use us as pawns of the Soul Society,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to eliminate us if we resist!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.96,0:15:35.24,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is bad…! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.03,0:15:37.48,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.48,0:15:38.92,Default,ISHIDA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There’s no way Kurosaki{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.92,0:15:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}can cope with these truths \Nin his present state!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:42.68,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,They all know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.68,0:15:47.84,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone in the Soul Society \Nbesides you knows this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.06,0:15:52.80,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,They abandoned you and \Nleft you to die, Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.80,0:15:54.26,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t listen to him, Kurosaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.26,0:15:55.47,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.62,0:16:08.23,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Bankai!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.10,0:16:19.55,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.55,0:16:20.83,Default,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,…Renji…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.27,0:16:22.79,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,You all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.79,0:16:25.08,Default,RENJI,0000,0000,0000,,Does it hurt anywhere?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:25.97,Default,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:27.84,Default,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, my right shoulder hurts…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.64,0:16:44.03,Default,RUKIA,0000,0000,0000,,Is Ichigo still inside…?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.53,0:16:54.91,Default,RUKIA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With this many captain-class \NSoul Reapers present, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}destroying that dimension \Nshould be easy…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:00.10,Default,RUKIA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get it… {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.10,0:17:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They’re waiting to see his decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.83,0:17:12.26,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,What?! What’s going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.26,0:17:13.54,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible…!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.54,0:17:15.22,Default,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s collapsing…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.51,0:17:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bankai.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.73,0:17:44.81,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,“Shut the hell up”?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.33,0:17:47.26,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up about what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.33,0:17:50.24,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Do I annoy you so much
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.24,0:17:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you’d do Bankai to kill \Nme at once to shut me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.80,0:17:55.56,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What would that do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.19,0:17:58.72,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Would that hide your eyes \Nfrom reality once more?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.71,0:18:00.89,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.31,0:18:05.24,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That one was towards you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:07.58,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But what I said earlier wasn’t…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.33,0:18:09.71,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It was towards Ishida.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.76,0:18:13.68,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,“Don’t listen to him, \NKurosaki!” my ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.68,0:18:14.93,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.93,0:18:16.57,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your own business!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.89,0:18:18.25,Default,ISHIDA,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.85,0:18:25.54,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I also thought what Ukitake \Nsaid to me sounded odd…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.54,0:18:26.72,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.58,0:18:29.64,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn’t want to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.19,0:18:33.42,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t want to suspect Ukitake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.96,0:18:38.46,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why I always shoved those \Nthoughts to the back of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.34,0:18:42.34,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But then I realized something…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.12,0:18:46.79,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I asked myself, “Why was \NI suspicious of Ukitake”?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.89,0:18:52.66,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Ukitake is a lot smarter than me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:56.32,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,If he really was planning to deceive me,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.26,0:19:00.39,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,he would have done so in a way \Nthat I wouldn’t notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.72,0:19:03.53,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But Ukitake handed me
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.53,0:19:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Combat Pass along \Nwith that explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:11.96,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,And I soon realized
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.55,0:19:15.76,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,that the Combat Pass had no function.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.67,0:19:21.57,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m guessing that Ukitake purposely
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.57,0:19:23.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,allowed me to realize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.41,0:19:26.05,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,He purposely let me come to that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.05,0:19:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,realization and make my own choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.77,0:19:29.93,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Regarding what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.93,0:19:31.35,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Coming to that realization
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.35,0:19:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,didn’t leave you any \Nchoice in the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.65,0:19:34.99,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I did make a choice…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.69,0:19:38.77,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I chose the path of protecting others.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.59,0:19:41.44,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.98,0:19:46.68,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted the power to protect all \Nsorts of people, all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.49,0:19:50.83,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,When I lost my powers, I \Nremembered that feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.45,0:19:55.92,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia gave me the power I \Nsought to protect people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.04,0:20:01.84,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone helped me regain \Nthe powers I had lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.32,0:20:08.31,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why I will protect \Neveryone and fight you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.83,0:20:13.82,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,There go the negotiations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:15.98,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You leave me no choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.23,0:20:19.99,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn’t want to have to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.34,0:20:22.61,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Bankai.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.69,0:20:43.58,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I forgot about that…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.58,0:20:46.26,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You were a Substitute Soul Reaper \Nyourself, weren’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.90,0:20:48.38,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.38,0:20:50.45,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,But there’s something else you forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.10,0:20:53.44,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,As I told you…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.44,0:20:55.15,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,People like us were
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,attacked by Hollows before we were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.13,0:21:00.44,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Inside me…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.25,0:21:03.90,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,is the power of a Hollow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.90,0:21:05.18,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.19,0:21:17.11,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it on, Ginjo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.11,0:21:18.79,Default,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s hurry up and settle this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.36,0:21:22.63,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,You talk big for a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:22.88,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Time will try to constantly \Ntry to catch up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.22,0:23:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And with a roar, it will overcome you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.30,0:23:28.07,Default,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Do not look ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.07,0:23:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope only lies within the unforeseeable
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.98,0:23:33.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,current that will close in from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.12,0:23:36.52,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Illustrated Guide to Soul Reapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.58,0:23:38.47,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.47,0:23:39.81,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.81,0:23:41.73,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,It’s me, everyone’s idol, Kon!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.24,0:23:44.46,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Since this is the last “Illustrated \NGuide to Soul Reapers,”
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.46,0:23:46.78,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll let you in on an interesting \Nstory about myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.40,0:23:50.94,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,After Ichigo lost his powers, \Nthese two were deeply troubled…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.94,0:23:53.24,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,“What could we do to help \Nhim?” they wondered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.76,0:23:56.24,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,This is what I told them:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.59,0:23:58.20,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,You guys need to have faith in Ichigo…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.20,0:23:59.85,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? We’re done?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.85,0:24:00.71,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the end?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.71,0:24:02.00,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,I was coming to the best part!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.00,0:24:04.75,Default,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!